---
const stack = [
  "Figma", "Framer", "Webflow", "Cursor",
  "Linear", "Notion", "Principle", "After Effects",
  "Protopie", "Storybook",
];
---

<section id="about" class="px-6 md:px-10 py-24 md:py-40 bg-[color:var(--color-ink)] text-[color:var(--color-paper)] relative overflow-hidden" data-cursor-mode="dark">
  <!-- Decorative oversized number -->
  <div class="pointer-events-none select-none absolute -bottom-16 -left-6 serif text-[28vw] md:text-[20vw] leading-none text-white/[0.04]">
    03
  </div>

  <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-[1280px] grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
    <div class="md:col-span-4 reveal">
      <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/50 mb-4">About — Long Story Short</div>
      <h2 class="serif text-5xl md:text-7xl text-balance">A designer, <em class="italic">first</em>.</h2>

      <!-- Circular monogram, Robert-style -->
      <div class="mt-12 hidden md:block">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 220 220" class="w-44 h-44">
          <defs>
            <path id="circle-text" d="M 110, 110 m -90, 0 a 90,90 0 1,1 180,0 a 90,90 0 1,1 -180,0" />
          </defs>
          <circle cx="110" cy="110" r="92" fill="none" stroke="white" stroke-opacity="0.2" stroke-width="1"/>
          <text font-size="11" fill="white" fill-opacity="0.6" letter-spacing="3" font-family="Inter, sans-serif">
            <textPath href="#circle-text" startOffset="0">
              MUHAMMED SARHAN ★ CAIRO, EGYPT ★ PRODUCT DESIGN ★ EST. 2014 ★
            </textPath>
          </text>
          <text x="50%" y="56%" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Instrument Serif" font-style="italic" font-size="64" fill="white">m</text>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="md:col-span-7 md:col-start-6 space-y-7 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/80 reveal">
      <p>
        I was born and raised in Cairo, and learned to design in print —
        where spacing is a moral position and a grid is only as good as the
        decisions it forces you to make. I fell into product when a client
        needed a website, and I never quite found my way back to paper.
      </p>
      <p>
        A decade later I'm still here, designing software from a desk in
        Cairo for teams across the Middle East, Europe, and North America.
        The work has spanned fintech, healthcare, e-commerce, government,
        on-demand, and a long list of digital media platforms whose names
        you'd recognise.
      </p>
      <p>
        I write code well enough to keep engineers honest, run my own
        research when I can, and care more about how a thing
        <em class="text-white not-italic">feels</em> than how it photographs.
        The best design decisions are the ones nobody notices.
      </p>

      <div class="pt-8 border-t border-white/15 grid grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/50 mb-3">Speaks</div>
          <div class="serif text-2xl">English · Arabic</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/50 mb-3">Reads</div>
          <div class="serif text-2xl">Type, brand books, complaints</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-8 border-t border-white/15">
        <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/50 mb-4">Toolkit</div>
        <ul class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          {stack.map((t) => (
            <li class="text-sm border border-white/20 rounded-full px-3 py-1">{t}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
